>>>>>>> Evaluation of your activity is an important part of the user
involvement process. You need to know if the work has been delivered
effectively and the impact it has had on diabetes care in your area.
>>>>>>> * Identify what works well and help think about how to do
>>>>>>> * Demonstrate the value of user involvement to senior staff
by showing how involvement is making a difference.
>>>>>>> * Share learning and improve the planning of future
>>>>>>> If you have access to expert staff, you may be able to do a thorough
>>>>>>> Once you’ve completed your evaluation, you’ll have a much better idea
of how to make involvement happen. Make sure you ask yourself:
>>>>>>> * How the lessons from the evaluation will be shared with
>>>>>>> * How you can make sure people act upon your
>>>>>>> * How progress on your recommendations will be monitored and
>>>>>>> * How you will do things differently for the next time you
>>>>>>> Sharing your experience will help others learn as well as celebrate
